 \"org.codehaus.btm:btm:2.1.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Ehcache documentation and DefaultTransactionManagerLookup support Bitronix as an automatically detected local transaction manager for JTA/XA coverage.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix has optional JMS API linkage that is not pulled transitively but is needed for reliable embedded Bitronix initialization on the test classpath.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Disable Ehcache's update checker in tests with System.setProperty(\\\"net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck\\\", \\\"true\\\") or Configuration.updateCheck(false). If exercising DefaultTransactionManagerLookup with Bitronix, create a temporary bitronix.properties file, set bitronix.tm.configuration to it, use bitronix.tm.disableJmx=true and bitronix.tm.journal=null, then shut down Bitronix and clear the property after the test. Use unique CacheManager/cache names and always shut managers down because Ehcache 2.5 enforces CacheManager name uniqueness in the VM.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Hibernate, servlet, and Terracotta integration classes are present in ehcache-core but depend on provided/external runtimes; avoid those paths unless explicitly adding the matching dependencies or service setup.\",\n    \"Disk persistence tests should use temporary directories and flush/shutdown managers to avoid cross-test state.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether these setup choices are sufficient.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0984fa8aa5b7e671016a42899b3ce08195846dce520e553a25\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 935, "output": 1022, "cacheRead": 45568, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47525, "cost": {"input": 